    <h3>Steffi</h3>
    <p>This morning we first headed to the outdoor shop we had spotted the evening before. There we got a new rod for our sun shade, and our journey continued toward the Great Ocean Road!</p>
    <p>Our first stop was a gas station before we hit the coastal road. We hadn't been on it for long when we were already pulling into the first parking area and heading down the steps. These led us to yet another deserted beach. We walked back and forth a bit, had fun in the water, and then the drink and food we had consumed demanded their tribute! We drove a few kilometers on and also hoped for restroom facilities. So back up in the car and on to the next stop. Once there, we did find restrooms, and there was also activity on and in the water. After watching the spectacle for a few minutes, we drove on.</p>
    <p>Our next destination was the Aireys Inlet lighthouse.</p>
