    <p>You could pay to go up to the lighthouse, but we skipped that and just walked along the path a bit and took a few good photos before continuing to the next section. However, I didn't notice much of this. I fell asleep again! *Stupid engine*!!!</p>
    <p>I was somewhat awake, but I didn't register much... except that the route was curvy and had some potholes, and somehow it was making my stomach uneasy.</p>
    <p>We soon reached our destination, Apollo Bay, and the campsite there. After checking in, we parked Hugo right by the pool. This would be our spot for the next two nights. In the evening, we didn't do much more except briefly jump in the pool and stop by the tourist information center. Then we went to bed because we both felt like we were coming down with a cold.</p>
    <p>But more about that tomorrow.<br>Good night.</p>
